    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Photographic paper on which the image is invisible, or latent, until it is brought out by a chemical developer after exposure to light, usually through a negative. Distinguished from 'printing-out paper' where the image is formed and immediately viewable while being exposed to light.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
